Design and develop a University Department Web Page using HTML that provides essential
information about a specific department (e.g., Computer Science, Mechanical Engineering).
The webpage should include a header section with the university name and its detailed
description and administrative heads. The main content should contain an About section
describing the department, along with details of courses offered, including course names and
brief descriptions. It can also include a Faculty section (optional) listing faculty member with
their names, designations, and areas of expertise (basic text is sufficient). Additionally, the
page should include a Contact section with details such as address, phone number, and email.
A footer section should be added with copyright information. Maintain the source code in a
GitHub repository [10].
• Clone the repository into VS Code, make any updates, commit and push the changes
to the Git repository [10].
• Containerize the application using Docker and prepare it for deployment [10].
• Configure Jenkins to create a pipeline project that builds, tests, and deploys the
application using Docker and Kubernetes, and visualize the deployment through
Docker Desktop [20].
